President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday night disclosed that his greatest happiness in the past four years is degrading Boko Haram. He spoke during an interview with NTA. The President also said that his administration is also happy with the economy. He said much progress has been made in the economy, especially in agriculture. Asked his greatest frustration, he said that it has to with inability to move faster against corruption. He said “We cannot be too much in a hurry.” 